# Scrape / local e2e testing

Prefer **local k3s e2e** over debugging scrape behavior only on the droplet.
Prove behavior before promote.

## Two e2e kinds (W7 — agreed)

| Kind | Command | Gate |
|------|---------|------|
| **Mocks** | `bun run check:e2e-mocks` | Automated — CI / PR |
| **Live** | `bun run preprod:e2e-online` | **Manual** — before prod scrape |

Live hits real Facebook and needs `~/.config/homie/facebook_state.json`.
Do **not** make live a blocking staging CI step.

## Safety / secrets

| Item | Rule |
|------|------|
| Facebook session | Out of band; never commit |
| Slack in e2e | Mocks: no live Slack (formatter tests only). Live: avoid treating as `#homie-runtime-errors` by default |
| PII / post bodies | Do not paste live scrape rows into git or chat |

## Local substrate

```bash
./scripts/k3s-local-up.sh
kubectl apply -k infra/k3s/overlays/local
cd scrapers/facebook
bun run check:postgres
bun run check:temporal
bun run check:e2e-mocks
```

Host ports: Postgres `127.0.0.1:54329`, Temporal `127.0.0.1:7233` — see `infra/README.md`.
